4
00:00:25.159 --> 00:00:27.404
{\an8}[gentle music playing]

5
00:00:27.428 --> 00:00:28.429
{\an8}Wallet?

6
00:00:29.096 --> 00:00:30.307
{\an8}Er. yes.

7
00:00:30.331 --> 00:00:31.575
{\an8}Coat.

8
00:00:31.599 --> 00:00:33.076
{\an8}Not in this weather.

9
00:00:33.100 --> 00:00:34.311
{\an8}Flask and sandwiches?

10
00:00:34.335 --> 00:00:36.613
{\an8}[sighs] It's 90 minutes away.
It's not Scotland.

11
00:00:36.637 --> 00:00:37.638
{\an8}Those for your mum?

12
00:00:43.444 --> 00:00:45.045
{\an8}I didn't want to turn up
empty-handed.

13
00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:47.248
{\an8}She ran out on you.

14
00:00:47.782 --> 00:00:49.292
{\an8}Again.

15
00:00:49.316 --> 00:00:53.687
{\an8}The point is to listen and...
not to shout or judge.

16
00:00:55.256 --> 00:00:58.168
{\an8}Be careful. London is full
of sinners and squalor.

17
00:00:58.192 --> 00:01:00.737
{\an8}[chuckles] I grew up there.
Romford is no more rife

18
00:01:00.761 --> 00:01:02.296
{\an8}with crime than Grantchester.

19
00:01:05.533 --> 00:01:06.534
{\an8}No.

20
00:01:11.572 --> 00:01:13.150
{\an8}No. no!

21
00:01:13.174 --> 00:01:15.142
{\an8}[woman] Oh. Alphy.
do you have a spare?

22
00:01:17.211 --> 00:01:18.379
{\an8}I don't have four.

23
00:01:19.413 --> 00:01:21.558
{\an8}You must call Geordie.

24
00:01:21.582 --> 00:01:23.527
{\an8}If I report this now.
I won't get away before lunch.

25
00:01:23.551 --> 00:01:24.594
{\an8}Oh. go another day.

26
00:01:24.618 --> 00:01:26.062
{\an8}No. no.
I can't keep putting this off.

27
00:01:26.086 --> 00:01:27.588
{\an8}I'm losing sleep
over it already.

28
00:01:29.323 --> 00:01:30.467
{\an8}[amusing music playing]

29
00:01:30.491 --> 00:01:31.525
{\an8}I can get a train.

30
00:01:32.359 --> 00:01:33.737
[chatter]

31
00:01:33.761 --> 00:01:35.162
[train whistles]

32
00:01:35.629 --> 00:01:36.630
[bell ringing]

33
00:01:38.833 --> 00:01:41.168
The village has fallen
into wrack and ruin.

34
00:01:41.635 --> 00:01:44.314
Vandalism. theft.

35
00:01:44.338 --> 00:01:48.251
Mr Everett from Number 6 is
growing a beard.

36
00:01:48.275 --> 00:01:49.853
Was Alphy okay?

37
00:01:49.877 --> 00:01:52.722
As if he didn't have enough
on his plate today already.

38
00:01:52.746 --> 00:01:54.381
Maybe I shouldn't have
found his mam.

39
00:01:56.150 --> 00:01:58.795
Oh. Geordie. Alphy
deserved to know her.

40
00:01:58.819 --> 00:02:00.387
I knew she was gonna
let him down.

41
00:02:01.188 --> 00:02:02.232
I saw the signs.

42
00:02:02.256 --> 00:02:04.167
Geordie. it'll be all right.

43
00:02:04.191 --> 00:02:05.626
Alphy's got his head screwed on.

44
00:02:07.661 --> 00:02:10.373
Miss Scott... need a couple
of uniforms over...

45
00:02:10.397 --> 00:02:11.699
So sorry. do excuse me.

46
00:02:13.667 --> 00:02:15.278
Few too many martinis.

47
00:02:15.302 --> 00:02:18.215
-Big night last night?
-No. end of last week.

48
00:02:18.239 --> 00:02:19.516
But they keep repeating on her.

49
00:02:19.540 --> 00:02:22.209
[orchestral music playing]

50
00:02:28.749 --> 00:02:29.750
Excuse me.

51
00:02:36.423 --> 00:02:37.491
Good day to you. sir.

52
00:02:38.893 --> 00:02:40.737
Could I venture a glance
at your ticket. sir?

53
00:02:40.761 --> 00:02:42.339
Er... of course.

54
00:02:42.363 --> 00:02:44.198
[whispers] Er... here you go.

55
00:02:45.266 --> 00:02:46.266
Eh...

56
00:02:47.635 --> 00:02:49.537
We should be in shortly
before 11:00.

57
00:02:52.339 --> 00:02:54.184
You have a wonderful journey.

58
00:02:54.208 --> 00:02:56.208
The views are completely
free of charge. [chuckles]

59
00:02:56.477 --> 00:02:57.521
Thanks for the tip.

60
00:02:57.545 --> 00:02:58.905
[Mr Birde]
All part of the service.

61
00:03:07.454 --> 00:03:09.199
[groans]

62
00:03:09.223 --> 00:03:10.500
I am so sorry.

63
00:03:10.524 --> 00:03:11.525
Apologies.

64
00:03:14.628 --> 00:03:15.629
[clears throat]

65
00:03:21.335 --> 00:03:24.581
Atkins has a lead
in the Saint Said's case.

66
00:03:24.605 --> 00:03:26.740
Oh...
Where have the Garibaldi's gone?

67
00:03:27.608 --> 00:03:29.476
They started tasting funny.

68
00:03:30.678 --> 00:03:32.346
-Funny how?
-Sort of metallic.

69
00:03:32.947 --> 00:03:33.948
[Geordie] Hmm.

70
00:03:36.317 --> 00:03:37.317
Miss Scott.

71
00:03:39.653 --> 00:03:41.364
[footsteps approaching]

72
00:03:41.388 --> 00:03:42.823
Please take a seat.

73
00:03:49.296 --> 00:03:50.896
How long have you been
in the family way?

74
00:03:52.700 --> 00:03:53.901
Why would you think that?

75
00:03:58.339 --> 00:03:59.419
Has someone said something?

76
00:04:02.276 --> 00:04:04.254
Yeah. I'm just
hazarding a guess.

77
00:04:04.278 --> 00:04:05.278
Four kids.

78
00:04:07.514 --> 00:04:09.550
My test results are due any day.

79
00:04:10.951 --> 00:04:11.986
You haven't told Larry.

80
00:04:13.921 --> 00:04:15.923
You haven't thought
about this eventuality?

81
00:04:17.024 --> 00:04:18.635
Never mind hiding your marriage.

82
00:04:18.659 --> 00:04:21.471
-once you start showing...
-Look. I know that. [inhales]

83
00:04:21.495 --> 00:04:24.474
-[sombre music playing]
-I want to keep working.

84
00:04:24.498 --> 00:04:26.843
Larry's preoccupied
with the sergeant's exams.

85
00:04:26.867 --> 00:04:29.436
-We're not ready.
-Nobody ever is.

86
00:04:32.039 --> 00:04:33.717
[man] Romford.

87
00:04:33.741 --> 00:04:36.010
All those for Romford.
a line here. please.

88
00:04:43.817 --> 00:04:44.818
[knocking]

89
00:04:49.790 --> 00:04:50.834
Oh.

90
00:04:50.858 --> 00:04:51.859
Hello.

91
00:04:53.460 --> 00:04:54.461
Yes?

92
00:04:55.362 --> 00:04:56.664
Is Mira Kohli in?

93
00:04:57.531 --> 00:04:58.599
Nope. Sorry.

94
00:04:59.633 --> 00:05:01.511
Er. do you know
when she'll be back?

95
00:05:01.535 --> 00:05:03.971
She sometimes comes home for
lunch. Otherwise. she's at work.

96
00:05:05.339 --> 00:05:06.907
Right. She prefers tulips.

97
00:05:08.575 --> 00:05:09.877
And Dad might object.

98
00:05:11.712 --> 00:05:13.356
Er...

99
00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:14.658
sorry. who are you?

100
00:05:14.682 --> 00:05:16.660
I'm her son. Rajesh.

101
00:05:16.684 --> 00:05:17.685
[sombre music playing]

102
00:05:18.952 --> 00:05:20.721
Y-You're Mira's son?

103
00:05:21.955 --> 00:05:23.057
How do you know her?

104
00:05:24.958 --> 00:05:25.959
I'm Alphy Kottaram.

105
00:05:28.962 --> 00:05:30.497
She's never mentioned me?

106
00:05:31.699 --> 00:05:32.776
No.

107
00:05:32.800 --> 00:05:34.034
I reckon I'd remember a vicar.

108
00:05:35.803 --> 00:05:36.880
Or is it fancy dress?

109
00:05:36.904 --> 00:05:39.349
An ironic comment
on Christianity

110
00:05:39.373 --> 00:05:41.742
as an oppressive tool
of colonialism.

111
00:05:43.610 --> 00:05:44.912
No. no. that's...

112
00:05:49.049 --> 00:05:50.384
I'm sorry to bother you.

113
00:05:56.724 --> 00:05:58.125
Geordie Keating.

114
00:05:58.358 --> 00:06:00.994
there is a terrible injustice
occurring this very instant.

115
00:06:02.963 --> 00:06:04.841
Witness spotted a lad
smashing wing mirrors

116
00:06:04.865 --> 00:06:06.476
all along Mill Way.

117
00:06:06.500 --> 00:06:09.012
So you just snatched
the first child you saw?

118
00:06:09.036 --> 00:06:11.514
A Mr Lowell
described a young male.

119
00:06:11.538 --> 00:06:14.775
maybe eight or nine. light hair.
beige shirt playing truant.

120
00:06:15.909 --> 00:06:17.721
That could be any boy
in the village.

121
00:06:17.745 --> 00:06:19.079
Said his name was Raymond Hayes.

122
00:06:20.047 --> 00:06:21.424
Oh.

123
00:06:21.448 --> 00:06:23.760
Which Mrs Chapman
also confirmed.

124
00:06:23.784 --> 00:06:24.785
Oh.

125
00:06:25.853 --> 00:06:28.131
Larry. get hold of his parents.

126
00:06:28.155 --> 00:06:32.392
Raymond's father is very ill
and his mother died years ago.

127
00:06:33.026 --> 00:06:34.161
He needs help.

128
00:06:34.394 --> 00:06:35.763
Not wild accusations.

129
00:06:37.397 --> 00:06:39.109
Then I'm sure you'd be happy
to sit in with Raymond

130
00:06:39.133 --> 00:06:41.001
while we get to
the bottom of this.

131
00:06:41.835 --> 00:06:42.836
Happily.

132
00:06:49.076 --> 00:06:50.878
[women chattering]

133
00:06:51.779 --> 00:06:52.846
[woman] Alphy?

134
00:06:53.914 --> 00:06:55.149
What are you doing here?

135
00:06:58.552 --> 00:06:59.586
I came to see you.

136
00:07:01.188 --> 00:07:03.590
To ask you
why you disappeared. again.

137
00:07:07.728 --> 00:07:09.773
But don't worry.
it's all very clear now.

138
00:07:09.797 --> 00:07:12.032
You...
You... you went to my house?

139
00:07:17.504 --> 00:07:18.915
-I met Rajesh.
-[gasps]

140
00:07:18.939 --> 00:07:21.151
Th-They...
They don't know about you.

141
00:07:21.175 --> 00:07:23.019
That was abundantly clear.

142
00:07:23.043 --> 00:07:25.145
-I'm so sorry. I...
-I-I have a brother...

143
00:07:26.680 --> 00:07:28.048
and you kept it from me.

144
00:07:29.516 --> 00:07:32.085
They... They're not ready
to find out.

145
00:07:33.654 --> 00:07:35.532
And when was I going to be ready
to find out?

146
00:07:35.556 --> 00:07:36.590
I don't know.

147
00:07:37.558 --> 00:07:39.102
- I'm so sorry.
- But I've got it.

148
00:07:39.126 --> 00:07:42.505
Thirty years.
of course you have a family.

149
00:07:42.529 --> 00:07:44.329
-But you lied to me.
-[sombre music playing]

150
00:07:44.731 --> 00:07:46.743
I-I couldn't tell you.

151
00:07:46.767 --> 00:07:48.578
So shame then.

152
00:07:48.602 --> 00:07:50.580
-I'm your dirty secret.
-No.

153
00:07:50.604 --> 00:07:52.005
Or is it this. huh?

154
00:07:54.474 --> 00:07:55.609
I don't understand it.

155
00:07:58.145 --> 00:08:01.090
An Indian man
being part of that church.

156
00:08:01.114 --> 00:08:03.226
You left me there...

157
00:08:03.250 --> 00:08:05.094
outside that church. remember?

158
00:08:05.118 --> 00:08:07.764
I was a child.

159
00:08:07.788 --> 00:08:11.825
I-I... I knew nothing about
missionaries and conversions.

160
00:08:13.026 --> 00:08:15.672
I-I'm so glad that
you are alive and...

161
00:08:15.696 --> 00:08:17.731
and... well and happy.

162
00:08:18.165 --> 00:08:19.199
But I just...

163
00:08:21.034 --> 00:08:22.069
I hate...

164
00:08:23.971 --> 00:08:25.606
that you didn't escape it.

165
00:08:26.940 --> 00:08:27.941
You hate it.

166
00:08:30.010 --> 00:08:32.088
But you've had 30 years
to correct your mistake.

167
00:08:32.112 --> 00:08:34.882
And in all that time. you didn't
check on me. not once.

168
00:08:44.057 --> 00:08:45.592
[sombre music continuing]

169
00:08:50.898 --> 00:08:52.165
[conductor blows whistle]

170
00:08:56.270 --> 00:08:57.814
Er. careful.

171
00:08:57.838 --> 00:09:00.083
I have preserves
from Fortnum's inside.

172
00:09:00.107 --> 00:09:01.918
And I don't want them spread
anywhere other than

173
00:09:01.942 --> 00:09:03.152
the scones at luncheon club.

174
00:09:03.176 --> 00:09:05.788
Or I'll see to it
that your next stop

175
00:09:05.812 --> 00:09:07.080
will be the benefits office.

176
00:09:10.751 --> 00:09:12.729
They can't
get away with this. Matty.

177
00:09:12.753 --> 00:09:14.197
It's just so unfair.

178
00:09:14.221 --> 00:09:17.834
Flora. not amongst the navvies
and the missionaries.

179
00:09:17.858 --> 00:09:20.570
Oh. you really can be
quite witless.

180
00:09:20.594 --> 00:09:23.773
I'm a saint for tolerating you
all these years.

181
00:09:23.797 --> 00:09:26.066
Excuse me. Sorry. Thank you.
[grunts]

182
00:09:29.136 --> 00:09:31.571
[conductor] Mind the doors.
Mind the doors.

183
00:09:33.674 --> 00:09:34.841
A "thanks" would be nice.

184
00:09:38.745 --> 00:09:39.746
[train whistle blows]

185
00:09:55.362 --> 00:09:58.241
[clears throat] Excuse me.
is anyone sitting here?

186
00:09:58.265 --> 00:10:00.133
No. please go ahead.

187
00:10:04.805 --> 00:10:07.116
Very polite of you to ask.

188
00:10:07.140 --> 00:10:08.918
[woman] You are supposed to.
aren't you?

189
00:10:08.942 --> 00:10:09.986
Not everyone does.

190
00:10:10.010 --> 00:10:11.854
I'd hate to steal
somebody's seat.

191
00:10:11.878 --> 00:10:13.856
[man] Or sit on an
invisible bunny rabbit.

192
00:10:13.880 --> 00:10:16.292
[woman] Can you imagine?
I'd be so embarrassed.

193
00:10:16.316 --> 00:10:17.360
[man] I can't imagine
that Harvey

194
00:10:17.384 --> 00:10:19.162
would be too impressed either.

195
00:10:19.186 --> 00:10:21.164
[woman] Do you think
he'd need a ticket?

196
00:10:21.188 --> 00:10:22.365
[man] Invisible rabbit?

197
00:10:22.389 --> 00:10:24.133
Ah. they're not
going to charge him.

198
00:10:24.157 --> 00:10:25.234
[woman laughs]

199
00:10:25.258 --> 00:10:26.903
[woman 2]
Where are you going to?

200
00:10:26.927 --> 00:10:27.928
[woman 3] Cambridge.

201
00:10:29.229 --> 00:10:31.140
Smashed windows
at Blakely's farm.

202
00:10:31.164 --> 00:10:35.745
threw rocks at a delivery truck.
vandalised a signpost.

203
00:10:35.769 --> 00:10:37.714
All that from just this spring.

204
00:10:37.738 --> 00:10:39.339
And all before your dad got ill?

205
00:10:41.074 --> 00:10:43.777
We tried the stern talking to.
clip round the ear.

206
00:10:45.045 --> 00:10:46.646
But now you're back in here.

207
00:10:47.714 --> 00:10:49.016
Mrs C called by earlier.

208
00:10:50.050 --> 00:10:52.219
Someone did for Alphy's tyres.

209
00:10:54.021 --> 00:10:55.655
That was a vicar's car.

210
00:10:56.890 --> 00:10:58.025
A good friend of mine.

211
00:10:59.059 --> 00:11:01.395
Today was a very
important day for him.

212
00:11:02.696 --> 00:11:03.864
Tell us. son...

213
00:11:04.664 --> 00:11:05.742
did you do it?

214
00:11:05.766 --> 00:11:07.434
Don't be intimidated. Raymond.

215
00:11:07.667 --> 00:11:10.137
Just be truthful.
and all will be well.

216
00:11:10.971 --> 00:11:11.972
I did it.

217
00:11:13.273 --> 00:11:14.708
I did all of them.

218
00:11:21.715 --> 00:11:22.916
Do you speak English?

219
00:11:24.017 --> 00:11:25.061
English?

220
00:11:25.085 --> 00:11:26.887
[woman]
I don't think shouting helps.

221
00:11:27.821 --> 00:11:29.289
-What's happening?
-Oh.

222
00:11:30.023 --> 00:11:32.068
Good. You do understand.

223
00:11:32.092 --> 00:11:33.736
We thought you might
be able to help.

224
00:11:33.760 --> 00:11:35.238
-There's a woman crying...
-[woman sobbing]

225
00:11:35.262 --> 00:11:36.963
has been for a while.

226
00:11:39.199 --> 00:11:43.103
If you really are a vicar. well.
maybe that's your sort of thing.

227
00:11:43.737 --> 00:11:45.281
Erm... [exhales]

228
00:11:45.305 --> 00:11:47.150
[clicks tongue]
Er. where are we?

229
00:11:47.174 --> 00:11:50.219
Broken down about 20 minutes
from Cambridge.

230
00:11:50.243 --> 00:11:53.423
-All right. [exhales]
-[woman sobbing]

231
00:11:53.447 --> 00:11:55.482
Fine. Leave it with me.

232
00:12:01.421 --> 00:12:02.465
Is everything all right?

233
00:12:02.489 --> 00:12:05.268
Oh. it... it's Matty.
I think that...

234
00:12:05.292 --> 00:12:07.027
I think that she's...
[continues sobbing]

235
00:12:08.195 --> 00:12:10.039
[tense music playing]

236
00:12:10.063 --> 00:12:11.398
-Matty?
-[gasps]

237
00:12:12.866 --> 00:12:13.867
Matty. can you hear me?

238
00:12:15.102 --> 00:12:16.136
Wake up. Matty.

239
00:12:18.972 --> 00:12:20.416
Come on. wake up.
How long has she been like this?

240
00:12:20.440 --> 00:12:22.209
-She's not breathing.
-[woman] Is she okay?

241
00:12:24.010 --> 00:12:25.011
[music intensifies]

242
00:12:28.215 --> 00:12:29.249
No.

243
00:12:31.384 --> 00:12:32.919
No. I'm afraid she's dead.

244
00:12:37.858 --> 00:12:41.204
[woman crying]

245
00:12:41.228 --> 00:12:43.439
-[music stops]
-[chair squeaks]

246
00:12:43.463 --> 00:12:45.065
-[typewriter clicking]
-[man groans]

247
00:12:49.436 --> 00:12:50.480
[telephone rings]

248
00:12:50.504 --> 00:12:53.273
Can I get you a drink?
A tea. a coffee?

249
00:12:55.275 --> 00:12:56.276
No?

250
00:12:56.943 --> 00:12:58.221
Suppose not.

251
00:12:58.245 --> 00:13:00.213
[intriguing music playing]

252
00:13:04.017 --> 00:13:05.097
Er. would you like to read?

253
00:13:05.952 --> 00:13:07.220
I have the new Burgess.

254
00:13:09.556 --> 00:13:11.491
[groans]

255
00:13:15.929 --> 00:13:17.864
This really shouldn't
be so difficult.

256
00:13:19.966 --> 00:13:21.001
[chair squeaking]

257
00:13:26.239 --> 00:13:28.441
Do you need a tinkle. poppet?

258
00:13:30.577 --> 00:13:32.913
Jen? Have you heard?

259
00:13:33.880 --> 00:13:35.448
-Our results are in.
-What?

260
00:13:36.416 --> 00:13:38.461
-How did you know?
-Atkins told me.

261
00:13:38.485 --> 00:13:39.929
Atkins?

262
00:13:39.953 --> 00:13:42.589
He's got a mate in Ely.
Had their letter today.

263
00:13:42.822 --> 00:13:44.291
-This could be it.
-[sighs]

264
00:13:45.058 --> 00:13:46.135
The sergeant's exam.

265
00:13:46.159 --> 00:13:48.061
Of course. What else?

266
00:13:49.196 --> 00:13:51.131
Er. the letters aren't here yet.

267
00:13:51.598 --> 00:13:53.200
Oh. okay.

268
00:13:54.134 --> 00:13:55.168
Maybe tomorrow.

269
00:14:04.844 --> 00:14:07.214
Raymond needs sympathy
and understanding.

270
00:14:08.848 --> 00:14:10.893
I know he's young
a-and his dad's ill.

271
00:14:10.917 --> 00:14:14.363
and it's all very sad...
But you don't know them.

272
00:14:14.387 --> 00:14:16.587
The whole family's bounced
in and out of here for years.

273
00:14:17.891 --> 00:14:21.037
Some people can't
change their nature.

274
00:14:21.061 --> 00:14:22.104
If we all give up on him.

275
00:14:22.128 --> 00:14:23.630
then he really doesn't
stand a chance.

276
00:14:23.863 --> 00:14:25.908
Well. the community disagrees.

277
00:14:25.932 --> 00:14:28.635
We've had dozens of complaints
about him from villagers.

278
00:14:30.070 --> 00:14:32.048
It's in his best interest

279
00:14:32.072 --> 00:14:34.608
that I let the juvenile court
decide his fate.

280
00:14:35.909 --> 00:14:38.044
[tense music playing]

281
00:14:55.328 --> 00:14:56.606
We need to alert the guard

282
00:14:56.630 --> 00:14:58.070
and see if there's
a doctor on board.

283
00:14:58.431 --> 00:14:59.431
I'll go.

284
00:15:03.903 --> 00:15:06.273
Best if the rest of us stay put.

285
00:15:08.008 --> 00:15:09.242
[door closes]

286
00:15:10.243 --> 00:15:11.523
-[sighs]
-[Alphy] I'm so sorry.

287
00:15:12.579 --> 00:15:14.614
You have my deepest
condolences. Miss...

288
00:15:15.482 --> 00:15:17.050
I'm Flora. Thank you.

289
00:15:18.585 --> 00:15:20.186
[indistinct chatter outside]

290
00:15:26.426 --> 00:15:28.537
Was Matty unwell?

291
00:15:28.561 --> 00:15:31.131
No. she never got ill.

292
00:15:37.003 --> 00:15:38.243
Where are you travelling today?

293
00:15:39.039 --> 00:15:41.317
On my way home to Cambridge.

294
00:15:41.341 --> 00:15:43.581
But he insisted we see the
new show at the Royal Academy.

295
00:15:49.182 --> 00:15:50.493
Would you like to pray
for her with me?

296
00:15:50.517 --> 00:15:51.594
[footsteps approaching]

297
00:15:51.618 --> 00:15:52.658
Here we all are. [exhales]

298
00:15:53.353 --> 00:15:54.487
And good day to you all.

299
00:15:55.655 --> 00:15:56.656
Oh.

300
00:15:59.225 --> 00:16:01.437
This is the unfortunate lady.

301
00:16:01.461 --> 00:16:04.464
-Er. her name is Matty...
-Matilda Garland.

302
00:16:08.034 --> 00:16:10.212
Probably her heart. poor dear.

303
00:16:10.236 --> 00:16:12.982
-All right. let's get you out.
-No. don't. don't.

304
00:16:13.006 --> 00:16:15.117
N-Never move a body.

305
00:16:15.141 --> 00:16:17.744
Well. not until the authorities
have seen her.

306
00:16:17.977 --> 00:16:19.446
Have some experience.
do you. sir?

307
00:16:20.413 --> 00:16:23.025
-A little.
-Really?

308
00:16:23.049 --> 00:16:25.995
I-I think that's right.
I've read that.

309
00:16:26.019 --> 00:16:28.030
How long do you suppose
we'll be stuck here for?

310
00:16:28.054 --> 00:16:31.534
While they suppose. I shall
confirm an answer for you

311
00:16:31.558 --> 00:16:33.636
when I've conversed
with the driver.

312
00:16:33.660 --> 00:16:35.428
Just stay put for now.
[grunts softly]

313
00:16:37.030 --> 00:16:38.398
Hey. didn't you hear him?

314
00:16:39.599 --> 00:16:40.643
-[suspenseful music playing]
-Come back.

315
00:16:40.667 --> 00:16:42.535
For God's sake. Boy. stop!

316
00:16:43.403 --> 00:16:44.404
[groans]

317
00:16:53.179 --> 00:16:54.179
What is it?

318
00:16:56.015 --> 00:16:58.260
How can I help Raymond?

319
00:16:58.284 --> 00:17:00.129
I can't go behind
Geordie's back.

320
00:17:00.153 --> 00:17:03.599
But can Geordie really just
throw a child into a boys' home?

321
00:17:03.623 --> 00:17:05.768
I shouldn't talk
to you about it.

322
00:17:05.792 --> 00:17:09.071
I've endured three interminably
long evenings

323
00:17:09.095 --> 00:17:11.741
of risk on your behalf
in the last fortnight.

324
00:17:11.765 --> 00:17:14.777
So. if you want to imperil
the Northwest Territory again.

325
00:17:14.801 --> 00:17:17.437
I suggest you aid me now.

326
00:17:21.341 --> 00:17:23.101
You have to look at
the welfare of the boy...

327
00:17:24.077 --> 00:17:26.589
and the welfare
of the community.

328
00:17:26.613 --> 00:17:29.525
I know they've
complained about him. but...

329
00:17:29.549 --> 00:17:31.317
could they be persuaded
to say...

330
00:17:32.218 --> 00:17:33.653
they prefer him to stick around?

331
00:17:55.375 --> 00:17:56.375
What is it?

332
00:17:57.577 --> 00:17:59.078
I was meant to pray for her.

333
00:18:02.282 --> 00:18:03.316
I've. er...

334
00:18:04.217 --> 00:18:05.285
I've had a dream about...

335
00:18:06.753 --> 00:18:07.821
praying for the dying.

336
00:18:14.093 --> 00:18:15.671
-[sombre music playing]
-Go forth from this world.

337
00:18:15.695 --> 00:18:17.363
in the love of God
who created you.

338
00:18:18.498 --> 00:18:19.499
in the mercy of...

339
00:18:21.434 --> 00:18:22.602
That was a short one.

340
00:18:25.538 --> 00:18:27.207
[suspenseful music playing]

341
00:18:28.274 --> 00:18:30.753
I thought you said
not to touch her.

342
00:18:30.777 --> 00:18:32.312
I said not to move her.

343
00:18:35.281 --> 00:18:36.616
There's blood on her fingers.

344
00:18:40.220 --> 00:18:41.497
You think she was killed?

345
00:18:41.521 --> 00:18:42.881
I think it's good
to ask questions.

346
00:18:46.226 --> 00:18:47.360
Beats sitting around.

347
00:18:51.865 --> 00:18:52.905
[woman] Any discoloration?

348
00:18:55.735 --> 00:18:58.214
[chuckles]
My father was a doctor.

349
00:18:58.238 --> 00:18:59.715
Redness for asphyxia.

350
00:18:59.739 --> 00:19:02.342
cherry or pink for cyanide.
brown for nitrates.

351
00:19:03.343 --> 00:19:04.820
Move over. Miss Marple.

352
00:19:04.844 --> 00:19:06.546
Hardly. [chuckles softly]

353
00:19:12.919 --> 00:19:14.387
-[music intensifies]
-[Alphy] Oh.

354
00:19:22.562 --> 00:19:24.707
Ah. it's metal.

355
00:19:24.731 --> 00:19:26.475
-[man] All right. Yeah. move it.
-[door closes]

356
00:19:26.499 --> 00:19:27.743
[man]
Hey. watch the jacket. man.

357
00:19:27.767 --> 00:19:29.487
-[Mr Birde] Shut it.
-You all right. love?

358
00:19:30.270 --> 00:19:31.313
Sit.

359
00:19:31.337 --> 00:19:32.906
We've got some
questions for you.

360
00:19:34.741 --> 00:19:36.719
-I've done nothing wrong.
-Then why'd you run. son?

361
00:19:36.743 --> 00:19:39.355
-Exercise.
-Yeah. more like fair dodgy.

362
00:19:39.379 --> 00:19:40.689
[man]
No. I always buy my tickets.

363
00:19:40.713 --> 00:19:42.791
Codswallop! You're bunking!

364
00:19:42.815 --> 00:19:44.484
[Alphy] Er. if I could have
a quick word.

365
00:19:48.755 --> 00:19:50.499
[woman] ...did you find out...
[indistinct]

366
00:19:50.523 --> 00:19:51.934
[whispering]
Matty Garland over there...

367
00:19:51.958 --> 00:19:54.360
I don't think she died
of natural causes.

368
00:19:55.495 --> 00:19:57.706
She had this in her arm.

369
00:19:57.730 --> 00:19:59.341
-[shouting] She was murdered?
-[man] What?

370
00:19:59.365 --> 00:20:00.543
Why do you think that?

371
00:20:00.567 --> 00:20:01.844
We found a wound on her.

372
00:20:01.868 --> 00:20:03.312
"We"?

373
00:20:03.336 --> 00:20:05.214
-Amelda?
-[Mr Birde] On my train.

374
00:20:05.238 --> 00:20:07.850
Good Lord.
What is this world coming to?

375
00:20:07.874 --> 00:20:08.918
-I should take that...
-[Alphy] Yeah.

376
00:20:08.942 --> 00:20:10.410
[Mr Birde] keep it as evidence.

377
00:20:11.411 --> 00:20:12.755
Can you contact the police?

378
00:20:12.779 --> 00:20:13.980
I only talked to the driver.

379
00:20:14.213 --> 00:20:15.824
find out what the holdup is.

380
00:20:15.848 --> 00:20:17.326
We're gonna be here a while.

381
00:20:17.350 --> 00:20:19.628
I'll walk to the next
signal post and telephone ahead.

382
00:20:19.652 --> 00:20:21.330
We should go over
everyone's movements.

383
00:20:21.354 --> 00:20:22.789
This isn't
a parlour game. vicar.

384
00:20:23.690 --> 00:20:24.691
I'm well aware.

385
00:20:26.426 --> 00:20:28.771
When was the last time
anyone saw Matty alive?

386
00:20:28.795 --> 00:20:30.806
Well. I came through
after Broxbourne.

387
00:20:30.830 --> 00:20:32.541
She asked me what time
we were due in at Cambridge.

388
00:20:32.565 --> 00:20:35.277
She was alive well after that.
I heard her after Audley End.

389
00:20:35.301 --> 00:20:36.469
That was the last stop.

390
00:20:37.303 --> 00:20:39.248
[dramatic music playing]

391
00:20:39.272 --> 00:20:40.649
Well. has anyone
from another carriage

392
00:20:40.673 --> 00:20:41.684
come through here since then?

393
00:20:41.708 --> 00:20:43.285
I don't think so.

394
00:20:43.309 --> 00:20:44.711
-Jack?
-No.

395
00:20:47.280 --> 00:20:50.016
You ran. you little rat!

396
00:20:50.249 --> 00:20:52.428
-I didn't do it!
-Let's not jump to conclusions.

397
00:20:52.452 --> 00:20:53.996
It's one of us.

398
00:20:54.020 --> 00:20:55.955
-And he ran.
-But we haven't spoken to Flora.

399
00:20:56.990 --> 00:20:58.458
She went to get a drink.

400
00:21:03.696 --> 00:21:05.975
[music intensifies]

401
00:21:05.999 --> 00:21:07.033
[sniffles]

402
00:21:09.869 --> 00:21:10.980
[door opens. clicks]

403
00:21:11.004 --> 00:21:13.373
[chuckles] I just needed
a minute to myself.

404
00:21:15.675 --> 00:21:17.953
We need to go back
to the other carriage. Flora.

405
00:21:17.977 --> 00:21:19.421
I don't want to.

406
00:21:19.445 --> 00:21:21.485
But we're trying to keep
everyone together. We're...

407
00:21:22.015 --> 00:21:23.349
We're all witnesses now.

408
00:21:24.917 --> 00:21:26.486
[sputters] Witnesses to what?

409
00:21:27.053 --> 00:21:28.797
[clicks tongue]

410
00:21:28.821 --> 00:21:30.690
Matty may not have died
of natural causes.

411
00:21:32.725 --> 00:21:34.360
Oh. God!

412
00:21:35.795 --> 00:21:38.898
No. no. no. I can't.

413
00:21:51.811 --> 00:21:53.379
Tell me what Matty was like.

414
00:21:55.748 --> 00:21:56.916
A force of nature.

415
00:21:58.484 --> 00:21:59.652
So sure of herself.

416
00:22:00.887 --> 00:22:02.831
Woe betide anyone
that stood in her way.

417
00:22:02.855 --> 00:22:03.890
Hmm.

418
00:22:06.426 --> 00:22:07.469
How long had you known her?

419
00:22:07.493 --> 00:22:08.895
Since our Wren days.

420
00:22:10.463 --> 00:22:11.597
She's my best friend.

421
00:22:12.932 --> 00:22:15.835
Was. No one else would have
a silly old thing like me.

422
00:22:17.470 --> 00:22:18.538
I doubt that.

423
00:22:23.576 --> 00:22:24.644
I...

424
00:22:25.678 --> 00:22:28.057
overheard you
talking about this.

425
00:22:28.081 --> 00:22:30.459
You were upset
by something in it?

426
00:22:30.483 --> 00:22:33.696
It... [sighs]
It's silly nonsense.

427
00:22:33.720 --> 00:22:35.464
There was an anonymous letter
in the paper

428
00:22:35.488 --> 00:22:36.856
questioning Matty's
charity work.

429
00:22:38.491 --> 00:22:39.735
Huh. Oh. yeah.

430
00:22:39.759 --> 00:22:42.495
"Self-aggrandising folly..."

431
00:22:43.763 --> 00:22:45.531
Ah. someone didn't like her.

432
00:22:46.399 --> 00:22:47.967
Like radish in a sandwich.

433
00:22:49.602 --> 00:22:52.081
-She was a strong flavour.
-Mm.

434
00:22:52.105 --> 00:22:54.707
Showed off a bit... [chuckles]
Like with her necklace.

435
00:22:56.476 --> 00:22:57.586
Er. necklace?

436
00:22:57.610 --> 00:22:59.846
Gold... with emeralds.

437
00:23:00.713 --> 00:23:02.014
Heirloom of the Raj.

438
00:23:02.749 --> 00:23:03.816
You must have noticed.

439
00:23:04.751 --> 00:23:06.786
-I must have.
-Worth a fortune.

440
00:23:08.054 --> 00:23:10.056
I said she was inviting
trouble wearing it.

441
00:23:12.458 --> 00:23:13.459
Hmm.

442
00:23:16.662 --> 00:23:17.797
What's that?

443
00:23:19.665 --> 00:23:21.610
-Ridley?
-I have no idea.

444
00:23:21.634 --> 00:23:23.645
Matty's writing.

445
00:23:23.669 --> 00:23:24.737
She loved a crossword.

446
00:23:25.505 --> 00:23:26.973
[footsteps approaching]

447
00:23:28.875 --> 00:23:30.419
The attendant in the buffet car

448
00:23:30.443 --> 00:23:32.121
can't recall anyone
else coming through.

449
00:23:32.145 --> 00:23:34.723
And no one's been in your
carriage in the last hour.

450
00:23:34.747 --> 00:23:37.860
Did... Matty leave her seat.
go anywhere?

451
00:23:37.884 --> 00:23:38.918
No.

452
00:23:40.553 --> 00:23:42.798
Well. once.

453
00:23:42.822 --> 00:23:45.100
Just after we broke down.
she went to get a tea

454
00:23:45.124 --> 00:23:46.769
and then came back
a minute later

455
00:23:46.793 --> 00:23:47.913
without one and then just...

456
00:23:48.995 --> 00:23:50.029
fell asleep.

457
00:23:54.000 --> 00:23:57.170
All of them...
withdrawn their statements?

458
00:23:58.504 --> 00:23:59.972
At the same time.

459
00:24:00.907 --> 00:24:02.575
Every single one.

460
00:24:05.978 --> 00:24:06.978
Leonard.

461
00:24:08.481 --> 00:24:09.582
[door opens]

462
00:24:11.951 --> 00:24:13.862
I really appreciate you
taking the time.

463
00:24:13.886 --> 00:24:14.887
Leonard.

464
00:24:16.856 --> 00:24:20.068
I could have you up for meddling
in police affairs.

465
00:24:20.092 --> 00:24:23.505
Mr Lowell and the others simply
agreed that handing the boy over

466
00:24:23.529 --> 00:24:26.175
to social services was not
in the best interest

467
00:24:26.199 --> 00:24:27.709
of the village.

468
00:24:27.733 --> 00:24:30.813
Until the next time he
vandalises or steals something.

469
00:24:30.837 --> 00:24:32.214
You're being very cynical.

470
00:24:32.238 --> 00:24:34.674
How many of your ex-cons
started like this?

471
00:24:39.612 --> 00:24:42.724
I put Raymond
into the care of the state.

472
00:24:42.748 --> 00:24:45.627
Maybe he doesn't end up
back here in five years

473
00:24:45.651 --> 00:24:47.663
for something much worse.

474
00:24:47.687 --> 00:24:51.500
Or maybe giving him a break now
gives him a chance to change.

475
00:24:51.524 --> 00:24:52.668
[sombre music playing]

476
00:24:52.692 --> 00:24:53.960
He's nine years old.

477
00:24:56.662 --> 00:24:57.997
On your head be it.

478
00:25:00.032 --> 00:25:02.134
but we both know
where good intentions lead.

479
00:25:10.910 --> 00:25:12.688
Ladies and gentlemen.

480
00:25:12.712 --> 00:25:14.790
I hope you'll understand
the imposition.

481
00:25:14.814 --> 00:25:16.959
But for the sake of everyone
else on this train.

482
00:25:16.983 --> 00:25:19.027
I'm afraid I must confine
you all to this carriage.

483
00:25:19.051 --> 00:25:20.262
With Matty?

484
00:25:20.286 --> 00:25:22.154
My apologies. but I insist.

485
00:25:23.823 --> 00:25:26.168
Driver says we're to be
at least another half hour here.

486
00:25:26.192 --> 00:25:28.237
And I would seek to preserve
the scene of the crime.

487
00:25:28.261 --> 00:25:29.341
Have you called the police?

488
00:25:29.528 --> 00:25:31.640
I'll pass the message
to Control.

489
00:25:31.664 --> 00:25:33.809
[keys jingle]

490
00:25:33.833 --> 00:25:36.612
God. he can't do this. can he?

491
00:25:36.636 --> 00:25:38.146
[Amelda] Hey. it's okay.

492
00:25:38.170 --> 00:25:39.882
You can't!

493
00:25:39.906 --> 00:25:41.783
You're locking us in
with the killer!

494
00:25:41.807 --> 00:25:43.886
[eerie music playing]

495
00:25:43.910 --> 00:25:45.578
[door locks]

496
00:25:50.650 --> 00:25:52.218
{\an8}Understood. Thanks.

497
00:25:53.853 --> 00:25:55.373
{\an8}Yes. we'll have someone
at the station.

498
00:25:56.589 --> 00:25:58.600
-Boss.
-Hmm?

499
00:25:58.624 --> 00:26:00.569
-Suspicious death on a train.
-[hangs up phone]

500
00:26:00.593 --> 00:26:02.137
I'll head over now.

501
00:26:02.161 --> 00:26:05.064
It's not in yet. Broken down
on its way back from London.

502
00:26:08.000 --> 00:26:09.135
Alphy's in London.

503
00:26:10.002 --> 00:26:11.647
Could be on it.

504
00:26:11.671 --> 00:26:13.282
You worried about him?

505
00:26:13.306 --> 00:26:16.251
No. of course not. [chuckles]

506
00:26:16.275 --> 00:26:18.086
No. he's down there
chasing his mum.

507
00:26:18.110 --> 00:26:20.155
For whatever that's worth.

508
00:26:20.179 --> 00:26:22.181
You know. some parents
do more harm than good.

509
00:26:23.783 --> 00:26:25.227
Not all.

510
00:26:25.251 --> 00:26:26.786
My mum. God rest her...

511
00:26:27.653 --> 00:26:28.864
she pushed me to be a copper.

512
00:26:28.888 --> 00:26:31.033
cheered me on
when no one else did.

513
00:26:31.057 --> 00:26:33.759
Would never have met Jen or you
without her.

514
00:26:39.198 --> 00:26:42.945
Raymond. you'll be able
to leave here shortly.

515
00:26:42.969 --> 00:26:44.980
If you'd like. I can
take you back home.

516
00:26:45.004 --> 00:26:47.182
Why?

517
00:26:47.206 --> 00:26:50.252
Well. I thought you might like
to be with someone you know.

518
00:26:50.276 --> 00:26:52.688
Why are they letting me go?

519
00:26:52.712 --> 00:26:55.657
I explained that
there were other factors

520
00:26:55.681 --> 00:26:57.025
affecting your behaviour.

521
00:26:57.049 --> 00:26:58.226
Why did you do that?

522
00:26:58.250 --> 00:27:01.296
Mr Finch is doing
something nice for you. Raymond.

523
00:27:01.320 --> 00:27:04.066
No. he's not. He's not nice.
he's sticking his nose in.

524
00:27:04.090 --> 00:27:06.902
-Raymond.
-You're not my dad!

525
00:27:06.926 --> 00:27:08.103
You're nobody!

526
00:27:08.127 --> 00:27:09.929
[sombre music playing]

527
00:27:12.264 --> 00:27:14.400
Mr Finch was trying to help you.

528
00:27:15.634 --> 00:27:17.379
Yeah. he's a good man.

529
00:27:17.403 --> 00:27:19.405
And you need
all the friends you can get.

530
00:27:19.638 --> 00:27:21.650
-Stop it!
-We're not doing anything.

531
00:27:21.674 --> 00:27:23.743
You keep talking all the time.

532
00:27:24.710 --> 00:27:26.855
I've stolen lots of things.

533
00:27:26.879 --> 00:27:28.748
Why aren't you doing your jobs?

534
00:27:36.655 --> 00:27:38.133
I. erm. [clears throat]

535
00:27:38.157 --> 00:27:41.136
I appreciate your time with
the distressed lady. vicar.

536
00:27:41.160 --> 00:27:44.306
And your... unexpected input.

537
00:27:44.330 --> 00:27:46.008
[sighs]

538
00:27:46.032 --> 00:27:47.342
Well. I have been around
a few crime scenes.

539
00:27:47.366 --> 00:27:49.811
-helped a few policemen.
-Hmm.

540
00:27:49.835 --> 00:27:51.246
There's one inspector
whose input

541
00:27:51.270 --> 00:27:52.681
would be a real help about now.

542
00:27:52.705 --> 00:27:54.206
Real jack of all trades.
aren't ya?

543
00:27:55.341 --> 00:27:59.054
Or Jamal. I suppose. [chuckles]

544
00:27:59.078 --> 00:28:02.948
[smirks] My guess is.
if it's not me. it's not you...

545
00:28:03.315 --> 00:28:05.027
it's not Amelda.

546
00:28:05.051 --> 00:28:07.763
Probably not that Flora. Then...

547
00:28:07.787 --> 00:28:09.197
it must be the lad.

548
00:28:09.221 --> 00:28:11.133
-Exactly.
-Hmm.

549
00:28:11.157 --> 00:28:13.201
Not the only amateur
detective in town.

550
00:28:13.225 --> 00:28:14.770
Mm.

551
00:28:14.794 --> 00:28:16.872
He's gonna slip up.

552
00:28:16.896 --> 00:28:18.256
[Alphy]
And you're gonna catch him.

553
00:28:32.278 --> 00:28:33.278
Her necklace is gone.

554
00:28:35.281 --> 00:28:36.916
I didn't see it
when we examined her.

555
00:28:37.750 --> 00:28:40.195
But it must be on the train.

556
00:28:40.219 --> 00:28:42.219
[Alphy] No. you're right.
I didn't see that before.

557
00:28:48.060 --> 00:28:51.097
I thought I should keep track
of what we know. For the police.

558
00:28:52.031 --> 00:28:54.900
Missing necklace. metal spike.

559
00:28:56.869 --> 00:28:59.281
[with Poirot's French accent]
Using my little grey cells.

560
00:28:59.305 --> 00:29:01.040
-[laughs]
-[Alphy chuckles]

561
00:29:05.177 --> 00:29:06.479
You're missing a ring.

562
00:29:08.314 --> 00:29:09.491
[in normal voice] Oh. of what?

563
00:29:09.515 --> 00:29:10.883
It's been stolen. too?

564
00:29:14.820 --> 00:29:15.821
[sighs]

565
00:29:21.327 --> 00:29:22.428
Ah. [chuckles softly]

566
00:29:24.163 --> 00:29:26.408
-So you're married?
-Are you disappointed?

567
00:29:26.432 --> 00:29:27.433
[scoffs]

568
00:29:33.072 --> 00:29:35.917
[Alphy] It's Jeff. isn't it?

569
00:29:35.941 --> 00:29:39.211
-Either he's your husband or...
-Or I'm having an affair.

570
00:29:39.879 --> 00:29:41.013
[exhales]

571
00:29:41.814 --> 00:29:43.358
Oh...

572
00:29:43.382 --> 00:29:45.784
A grubby little word
when you say it out loud.

573
00:29:48.521 --> 00:29:53.135
I married
my childhood sweetheart. Harry.

574
00:29:53.159 --> 00:29:56.438
And I guess
if you do it long enough.

575
00:29:56.462 --> 00:29:58.264
even bliss becomes routine.

576
00:29:59.565 --> 00:30:03.979
Trapped in the same day.
living it over and over.

577
00:30:04.003 --> 00:30:05.871
And Jeff's an escape from that.

578
00:30:07.439 --> 00:30:09.117
You're a very perceptive man.

579
00:30:09.141 --> 00:30:11.019
[laughs]

580
00:30:11.043 --> 00:30:14.356
Well. this would
make me one-all today.

581
00:30:14.380 --> 00:30:16.358
For having the
wool pulled over my eyes.

582
00:30:16.382 --> 00:30:17.383
Oh.

583
00:30:18.350 --> 00:30:19.485
-I'm sorry.
-I...

584
00:30:21.287 --> 00:30:22.821
I trusted someone with a...

585
00:30:24.056 --> 00:30:27.068
bad track record.
It's stupid and naive.

586
00:30:27.092 --> 00:30:29.862
Don't be so hard on yourself
for being optimistic.

587
00:30:31.263 --> 00:30:32.263
We all need hope.

588
00:30:32.932 --> 00:30:33.933
[softly] Hmm.

589
00:30:35.901 --> 00:30:37.303
You must think terribly of me.

590
00:30:38.504 --> 00:30:39.972
I think lies hurt people.

591
00:30:41.207 --> 00:30:42.608
People like your husband.

592
00:30:46.111 --> 00:30:48.231
I think she'd share some of
that chocolate? [chuckles]

593
00:30:49.949 --> 00:30:51.884
-I think she's diabetic.
-[both chuckle]

594
00:30:55.221 --> 00:30:57.232
[tense music playing]

595
00:30:57.256 --> 00:30:59.158
So she could have a needle.

596
00:31:03.596 --> 00:31:05.030
We need to check her case.

597
00:31:08.167 --> 00:31:11.170
Hey. I need to speak
to the guard.

598
00:31:14.640 --> 00:31:16.075
You tried. Leonard.

599
00:31:17.076 --> 00:31:18.077
Let us deal with it now.

600
00:31:19.411 --> 00:31:22.891
-Most kids aren't like that.
-[Leonard] Are you sure?

601
00:31:22.915 --> 00:31:24.960
They're given
toy guns and swords.

602
00:31:24.984 --> 00:31:26.986
and we wonder
why they raise their fists.

603
00:31:27.653 --> 00:31:29.564
Maybe Geordie's right.

604
00:31:29.588 --> 00:31:32.634
Maybe our prisons
are full of Raymonds...

605
00:31:32.658 --> 00:31:34.059
destined for violence.

606
00:31:39.498 --> 00:31:40.498
[Larry] I had a spud gun.

607
00:31:41.367 --> 00:31:42.468
I turned out all right.

608
00:31:50.042 --> 00:31:51.076
[Miss Scott] Oh.

609
00:31:54.113 --> 00:31:55.147
I'm sorry.

610
00:31:56.115 --> 00:31:57.492
[Geordie] Don't be.

611
00:31:57.516 --> 00:31:59.184
Tough day. right?

612
00:32:04.189 --> 00:32:06.058
That poor child.

613
00:32:07.259 --> 00:32:08.603
Not all kids are like that.

614
00:32:08.627 --> 00:32:10.405
They could be. though.

615
00:32:10.429 --> 00:32:13.666
That's the risk. isn't it?
I-If you... get it wrong...

616
00:32:17.569 --> 00:32:18.637
You get everything wrong.

617
00:32:19.571 --> 00:32:22.550
No matter how hard you try.

618
00:32:22.574 --> 00:32:26.054
You'll worry about it
for the rest of your days. Hmm.

619
00:32:26.078 --> 00:32:28.314
Well. brilliant pep talk.
Thanks.

620
00:32:31.083 --> 00:32:32.184
[chuckles]

621
00:32:33.452 --> 00:32:34.453
You know. my dad...

622
00:32:35.421 --> 00:32:37.198
wasn't much cop.

623
00:32:37.222 --> 00:32:40.268
And Alphy was raised
by the state.

624
00:32:40.292 --> 00:32:42.461
But sometimes kids get by
despite their parents.

625
00:32:46.131 --> 00:32:48.534
Maybe this is just a scare.

626
00:32:51.570 --> 00:32:53.472
A chance to think
about what you want.

627
00:33:01.714 --> 00:33:04.283
Mrs Garland and Mrs Crabtree's.

628
00:33:07.252 --> 00:33:08.252
[case clicks open]

629
00:33:09.588 --> 00:33:11.666
[Alphy] That must be Flora's
medical case.

630
00:33:11.690 --> 00:33:12.810
[Mr Birde] This kinda thing.

631
00:33:14.493 --> 00:33:17.172
Well. there's the insulin.
There should be a syringe.

632
00:33:17.196 --> 00:33:18.556
Well. as you can see.
there is not.

633
00:33:19.698 --> 00:33:21.609
I've held on to something
in lost property

634
00:33:21.633 --> 00:33:23.035
that might prove useful.

635
00:33:39.685 --> 00:33:43.055
You wouldn't believe what gets
left or thrown away on here.

636
00:33:45.524 --> 00:33:47.435
Or maybe the syringe
was thrown away.

637
00:33:47.459 --> 00:33:48.761
[suspenseful music playing]

638
00:33:49.495 --> 00:33:50.496
[Alphy grunts]

639
00:33:59.571 --> 00:34:02.317
[softly] Okay. It should be...

640
00:34:02.341 --> 00:34:04.152
You do realise you are literally

641
00:34:04.176 --> 00:34:06.779
looking for a needle
in a deconstructed haystack?

642
00:34:09.081 --> 00:34:10.416
[music intensifies]

643
00:34:26.532 --> 00:34:27.609
[music fades]

644
00:34:27.633 --> 00:34:29.635
You can't kill someone
with insulin.

645
00:34:30.402 --> 00:34:31.479
Can you?

646
00:34:31.503 --> 00:34:33.615
You could put poison in it.

647
00:34:33.639 --> 00:34:36.108
Or you could simply
inject Matty with air.

648
00:34:37.276 --> 00:34:39.411
-Give her an air embolism.
-[Jeff] Good God.

649
00:34:42.648 --> 00:34:43.782
Well. it wasn't me.

650
00:34:45.184 --> 00:34:46.452
She was my friend.

651
00:34:47.686 --> 00:34:50.799
Someone's been through
my things. my medicine.

652
00:34:50.823 --> 00:34:54.536
We know Matty left her seat
just after the train stopped.

653
00:34:54.560 --> 00:34:56.528
but never got
to the buffet carriage.

654
00:34:58.263 --> 00:35:01.600
She could have been confronted
and injected there...

655
00:35:02.434 --> 00:35:03.435
in the gangway.

656
00:35:05.370 --> 00:35:06.672
And the syringe thrown out.

657
00:35:11.677 --> 00:35:13.579
Can you all stop looking at me?

658
00:35:16.281 --> 00:35:17.483
Matty was...

659
00:35:18.550 --> 00:35:20.295
a big character.

660
00:35:20.319 --> 00:35:21.596
-She was my best friend.
-[tense music resumes]

661
00:35:21.620 --> 00:35:23.698
A best friend
that belittles you...

662
00:35:23.722 --> 00:35:24.790
bullies you?

663
00:35:26.859 --> 00:35:29.328
Well. maybe she needed
taking down a peg or two.

664
00:35:33.165 --> 00:35:34.800
With a damning letter
to the paper.

665
00:35:41.607 --> 00:35:42.608
[scoffs]

666
00:35:44.543 --> 00:35:48.690
It was just a silly letter to
take the wind out of her sails.

667
00:35:48.714 --> 00:35:51.917
To not be the be all and the
end all. if only for a moment.

668
00:35:52.150 --> 00:35:55.697
If she twigged it was you.
maybe she got angry.

669
00:35:55.721 --> 00:35:57.765
Woe betide anyone
who stood in her way.

670
00:35:57.789 --> 00:35:59.267
No.

671
00:35:59.291 --> 00:36:01.736
What about the necklace.
Amelda says it's missing.

672
00:36:01.760 --> 00:36:03.929
-Did you take that. too?
-No. I didn't.

673
00:36:04.162 --> 00:36:05.531
I told you about that.

674
00:36:10.369 --> 00:36:11.446
-[sombre music playing]
-Damn you all.

675
00:36:11.470 --> 00:36:13.281
Please. Mrs Crabtree.

676
00:36:13.305 --> 00:36:14.840
[Flora] I don't have it.

677
00:36:16.375 --> 00:36:19.921
I am not a killer or a thief.

678
00:36:19.945 --> 00:36:21.313
I am just a doormat.

679
00:36:22.548 --> 00:36:25.426
A pathetic doormat.

680
00:36:25.450 --> 00:36:26.890
[voice falters]
And I always will be.

681
00:36:30.622 --> 00:36:31.623
[strangled sob]

682
00:36:35.928 --> 00:36:37.805
[exhales]

683
00:36:37.829 --> 00:36:39.574
There's always pickpockets
on this route.

684
00:36:39.598 --> 00:36:40.708
[Jeff] Do shut up.

685
00:36:40.732 --> 00:36:42.810
I'm just saying.
It could be anyone.

686
00:36:42.834 --> 00:36:43.834
He knows.

687
00:36:45.237 --> 00:36:46.438
He ran. didn't he?

688
00:36:47.339 --> 00:36:48.883
Because he killed Matty.

689
00:36:48.907 --> 00:36:51.386
-What?
-He knows where the necklace is.

690
00:36:51.410 --> 00:36:52.954
I was just
tryna make you feel better.

691
00:36:52.978 --> 00:36:56.214
There's a very simple solution.
Turn out your pockets.

692
00:36:56.682 --> 00:36:57.859
No.

693
00:36:57.883 --> 00:36:59.661
[Amelda] It would put
all our minds at ease.

694
00:36:59.685 --> 00:37:02.730
-If you would.
-Hey. sod off!

695
00:37:02.754 --> 00:37:06.358
Oi. we have a right to know if
there's a murderer amongst us.

696
00:37:09.561 --> 00:37:11.597
[tense music playing]

697
00:37:15.767 --> 00:37:16.802
[music intensifies]

698
00:37:22.674 --> 00:37:23.718
You're bloody happy now?

699
00:37:23.742 --> 00:37:25.587
[Jeff] Well. [clears throat]

700
00:37:25.611 --> 00:37:26.654
I'm not hiding anything.

701
00:37:26.678 --> 00:37:28.289
Nor I.

702
00:37:28.313 --> 00:37:30.291
Not a pretty sight.

703
00:37:30.315 --> 00:37:33.461
Too many old tickets
and sweet wrappers.

704
00:37:33.485 --> 00:37:35.587
-[music intensifies]
-Now you. vicar.

705
00:37:49.635 --> 00:37:50.636
[music fades]

706
00:37:52.671 --> 00:37:54.616
[Jeff] A con man in a costume.

707
00:37:54.640 --> 00:37:57.485
who pulled the wool
over all our eyes.

708
00:37:57.509 --> 00:37:59.721
You have those cuffs handy.
Mr Birde?

709
00:37:59.745 --> 00:38:01.823
I-I didn't hide it.
I showed you more.

710
00:38:01.847 --> 00:38:03.625
It was planted in my pocket.

711
00:38:03.649 --> 00:38:05.627
Do you think we're fools. hmm?

712
00:38:05.651 --> 00:38:06.961
[Jeff] Do you think
we're stupid enough

713
00:38:06.985 --> 00:38:09.998
that we buy the idea of
a crime-solving. Indian vicar?

714
00:38:10.022 --> 00:38:11.657
I am a vicar.

715
00:38:13.358 --> 00:38:14.469
I never lied to you.

716
00:38:14.493 --> 00:38:16.738
[Jeff] I should have
trusted my instincts.

717
00:38:16.762 --> 00:38:18.063
No. get off. Stop it!

718
00:38:18.296 --> 00:38:19.474
-Don't.
-[Amelda] He's been helping us.

719
00:38:19.498 --> 00:38:20.675
-He's not one of us.
-[Alphy groans]

720
00:38:20.699 --> 00:38:22.477
-[handcuff clicks]
-[sighs]

721
00:38:22.501 --> 00:38:25.446
I was asleep when Matty died.
You know I didn't kill her.

722
00:38:25.470 --> 00:38:26.648
Do we? Do we know that?

723
00:38:26.672 --> 00:38:29.050
[Jeff] We welcome foreigners
into this country.

724
00:38:29.074 --> 00:38:30.618
and this is what happens.

725
00:38:30.642 --> 00:38:32.553
Oh. not that old toss. Jeff.

726
00:38:32.577 --> 00:38:34.756
[Jeff] I'm not saying I like it.
but open your eyes.

727
00:38:34.780 --> 00:38:36.724
You were young. naive.
You've got no clue

728
00:38:36.748 --> 00:38:38.588
what these colonials
are doing to this country.

729
00:38:40.318 --> 00:38:43.388
I am married to a colonial.

730
00:38:44.956 --> 00:38:46.725
Harry's from the West Indies.

731
00:38:47.793 --> 00:38:49.033
And yet. who you sleeping with?

732
00:38:50.595 --> 00:38:52.564
You can be such an arse.

733
00:38:57.035 --> 00:38:59.004
[suspenseful music resumes]

734
00:39:01.473 --> 00:39:02.474
This is yours.

735
00:39:03.875 --> 00:39:06.044
I've seen these before
in your office.

736
00:39:07.846 --> 00:39:09.681
The necklace was in here.

737
00:39:12.417 --> 00:39:13.995
You planted it on me.

738
00:39:14.019 --> 00:39:15.797
[scoffs] I did not.

739
00:39:15.821 --> 00:39:17.665
Ask him for a look
in his little office.

740
00:39:17.689 --> 00:39:19.033
There's a dozen more of these.

741
00:39:19.057 --> 00:39:22.003
Enough! He'll say anything.

742
00:39:22.027 --> 00:39:24.639
Stringing us along
with his amateur detective tosh.

743
00:39:24.663 --> 00:39:27.008
I promise you all.
he is your thief.

744
00:39:27.032 --> 00:39:28.543
Enough!

745
00:39:28.567 --> 00:39:30.611
I'm the guardian of this train.
I have authority here.

746
00:39:30.635 --> 00:39:31.879
You are a liar.

747
00:39:31.903 --> 00:39:33.381
And you're no reverend.

748
00:39:33.405 --> 00:39:34.449
-[gasps]
-Whoa!

749
00:39:34.473 --> 00:39:35.983
-[Alphy groans]
-[dramatic sting]

750
00:39:36.007 --> 00:39:38.543
[scoff] Poking and prodding
and questioning.

751
00:39:40.812 --> 00:39:42.390
We've heard enough from you.
Come on.

752
00:39:42.414 --> 00:39:43.791
-Cuff the other hand.
-Get off!

753
00:39:43.815 --> 00:39:46.818
You know what? There are always
pickpockets on your route.

754
00:39:48.053 --> 00:39:49.130
[suspenseful music resumes]

755
00:39:49.154 --> 00:39:51.065
-I wanna see your office.
-Sit down. son.

756
00:39:51.089 --> 00:39:52.567
-I wanna see...
-[guard scoffs]

757
00:39:52.591 --> 00:39:55.136
-like the preacher man said.
-[Mr Birde] Really?

758
00:39:55.160 --> 00:39:58.096
-Fare dodgers giving orders now.
-[chuckles]

759
00:39:58.930 --> 00:40:00.708
He won't show us.

760
00:40:00.732 --> 00:40:03.778
He did bloody steal it. and
he probably killed the old girl.

761
00:40:03.802 --> 00:40:05.604
Sit yourself down.

762
00:40:06.872 --> 00:40:07.973
You never showed us that.

763
00:40:10.041 --> 00:40:11.753
You never showed us
your pockets.

764
00:40:11.777 --> 00:40:13.654
-Hey!
-[scoffs]

765
00:40:13.678 --> 00:40:17.558
I told you.
he robs the passengers.

766
00:40:17.582 --> 00:40:19.494
You took it off. Matty.
just after she died.

767
00:40:19.518 --> 00:40:20.518
Can you explain this?

768
00:40:21.720 --> 00:40:24.098
-Well. now. let's not be hasty.
-You owe us that.

769
00:40:24.122 --> 00:40:26.768
I'm really curious.
Mr Authority.

770
00:40:26.792 --> 00:40:28.059
Mm-hmm.

771
00:40:31.696 --> 00:40:34.041
I've been on the railway
since I was demobbed.

772
00:40:34.065 --> 00:40:36.110
Giving it
the best years of my life.

773
00:40:36.134 --> 00:40:39.013
And now the bosses want
to axe half the lines.

774
00:40:39.037 --> 00:40:41.449
Put people like me out
and they're here.

775
00:40:41.473 --> 00:40:43.184
All right.
so maybe not everything

776
00:40:43.208 --> 00:40:44.776
made its way to lost property.

777
00:40:46.044 --> 00:40:47.445
But I'm no murderer.

778
00:40:51.550 --> 00:40:52.551
[knocking on door]

779
00:40:55.520 --> 00:40:57.532
You were right.

780
00:40:57.556 --> 00:41:01.135
My... optimism about Raymond
was naive.

781
00:41:01.159 --> 00:41:02.194
No. it wasn't.

782
00:41:03.895 --> 00:41:05.940
The world needs people
like you to stop

783
00:41:05.964 --> 00:41:07.833
people like me
getting too cynical.

784
00:41:09.701 --> 00:41:11.746
We're both missing
the bigger issue here.

785
00:41:11.770 --> 00:41:12.771
What's that?

786
00:41:15.941 --> 00:41:17.552
That boy is sure as hell

787
00:41:17.576 --> 00:41:19.845
isn't looking for a way
out of this station.

788
00:41:47.105 --> 00:41:48.607
What you're going through...

789
00:41:50.108 --> 00:41:51.509
it's very unfair.

790
00:41:55.647 --> 00:41:57.883
My mum got ill
when I was very young.

791
00:41:58.717 --> 00:41:59.718
And...

792
00:42:00.619 --> 00:42:01.929
my dad wasn't around

793
00:42:01.953 --> 00:42:03.121
and I struggled.

794
00:42:04.589 --> 00:42:06.033
Were you sad?

795
00:42:06.057 --> 00:42:07.057
[Leonard] Yes.

796
00:42:08.026 --> 00:42:09.561
And lonely.

797
00:42:11.796 --> 00:42:12.864
Do you feel that?

798
00:42:18.136 --> 00:42:20.281
[Raymond]
I talk to Mum sometimes.

799
00:42:20.305 --> 00:42:21.840
She's in the churchyard.

800
00:42:23.208 --> 00:42:24.728
-[sombre music playing]
-At the back.

801
00:42:25.644 --> 00:42:27.822
[Leonard] I think that's lovely.

802
00:42:27.846 --> 00:42:29.246
It doesn't help Dad though.
does it?

803
00:42:30.582 --> 00:42:32.751
You are helping your dad.

804
00:42:33.752 --> 00:42:35.930
You're doing so much for him.

805
00:42:35.954 --> 00:42:37.188
He's getting worse.

806
00:42:38.089 --> 00:42:40.134
He can't look after me too.

807
00:42:40.158 --> 00:42:43.704
[Leonard] You think it would
help him if you weren't around?

808
00:42:43.728 --> 00:42:45.606
-If you were here?
-[Raymond] Course it would.

809
00:42:45.630 --> 00:42:47.098
My cousin's at a borstal.

810
00:42:47.999 --> 00:42:49.701
They have meals and beds.

811
00:42:50.669 --> 00:42:52.304
We can do better than that.

812
00:42:53.204 --> 00:42:55.116
Raymond?

813
00:42:55.140 --> 00:42:57.585
We're going to do
better than that.

814
00:42:57.609 --> 00:42:59.129
-I swear to you.
-[music intensifies]

815
00:43:06.952 --> 00:43:08.787
[exhales]

816
00:43:10.889 --> 00:43:12.223
Is Raymond going to be okay?

817
00:43:14.359 --> 00:43:16.671
Yeah. I was wrong about him.

818
00:43:16.695 --> 00:43:19.240
You wanted the best for him.

819
00:43:19.264 --> 00:43:22.009
Hmm. I wanted shot of him
before he slashed my tyres.

820
00:43:22.033 --> 00:43:23.033
You cared...

821
00:43:23.868 --> 00:43:25.003
and you listened.

822
00:43:26.705 --> 00:43:29.050
Alphy usually does that.

823
00:43:29.074 --> 00:43:30.952
You don't always need to run
around the country

824
00:43:30.976 --> 00:43:32.296
with a vicar
to make a difference.

825
00:43:32.944 --> 00:43:33.944
Maybe not.

826
00:43:40.952 --> 00:43:43.030
If it were up to me.

827
00:43:43.054 --> 00:43:45.123
you'd be a shoo-in
for the chief inspector job.

828
00:43:46.091 --> 00:43:47.802
[amusing music playing]

829
00:43:47.826 --> 00:43:49.160
The secretaries
do like a gossip.

830
00:43:52.330 --> 00:43:54.199
[footsteps receding]

831
00:43:58.003 --> 00:44:00.305
[eerie music playing]

832
00:44:10.715 --> 00:44:12.417
[Amelda]
How are you feeling now?

833
00:44:12.650 --> 00:44:15.153
Much like how a football
feels after a match.

834
00:44:17.088 --> 00:44:18.368
Tomorrow could always be better.

835
00:44:19.891 --> 00:44:20.925
Don't lose hope.

836
00:44:22.427 --> 00:44:24.705
This might sting.

837
00:44:24.729 --> 00:44:26.707
Those five years of medical
school really paid off.

838
00:44:26.731 --> 00:44:30.435
[laughs] I told you
my dad was a doctor.

839
00:44:31.669 --> 00:44:32.904
{\an8}Dr Ridley.

840
00:44:34.973 --> 00:44:37.151
[tense music playing]

841
00:44:37.175 --> 00:44:38.176
Ridley.

842
00:44:41.079 --> 00:44:42.414
[Alphy]
<i>She knew your family name.</i>

843
00:44:45.250 --> 00:44:46.250
Matty knew you.

844
00:44:47.385 --> 00:44:50.021
[tense music continues]

845
00:44:53.925 --> 00:44:55.794
<i>She knew you were
having an affair.</i>

846
00:44:57.295 --> 00:44:59.364
[sputters] I-I needed this.

847
00:45:00.965 --> 00:45:02.467
This escape. I...

848
00:45:04.402 --> 00:45:05.970
I wasn't ready for it to end.

849
00:45:08.106 --> 00:45:09.874
You needed her silence.

850
00:45:14.712 --> 00:45:16.891
Please. Please. I'm begging you.

851
00:45:16.915 --> 00:45:18.995
[Alphy] <i>You needed to know
she wouldn't say anything.</i>

852
00:45:20.752 --> 00:45:22.830
And you knew enough
about medicine

853
00:45:22.854 --> 00:45:24.823
to recognise Flora's diabetes.

854
00:45:25.757 --> 00:45:27.001
[Matty groans]

855
00:45:27.025 --> 00:45:28.860
[Alphy] <i>That she'd have
a syringe with her.</i>

856
00:45:34.232 --> 00:45:36.101
<i>And what an air embolism
could do.</i>

857
00:45:38.970 --> 00:45:42.941
{\an8}If she told Harry.
I would lose everything.

858
00:45:44.476 --> 00:45:45.920
People would talk. I...

859
00:45:45.944 --> 00:45:48.055
She would ruin my life.

860
00:45:48.079 --> 00:45:49.481
Your fantasy life.

861
00:45:51.516 --> 00:45:52.851
How does that look now?

862
00:45:55.286 --> 00:45:56.321
Was Jeff worth it?

863
00:46:02.293 --> 00:46:03.328
[Amelda sniffling softly]

864
00:46:05.330 --> 00:46:06.764
[train whistle blows]

865
00:46:23.515 --> 00:46:24.916
Larry!

866
00:46:31.289 --> 00:46:32.290
Yes. boss?

867
00:46:33.491 --> 00:46:35.527
You've got
some explaining to do.

868
00:46:37.562 --> 00:46:40.074
I have received
a very disturbing letter

869
00:46:40.098 --> 00:46:43.477
regarding the behaviour
of an officer in this force.

870
00:46:43.501 --> 00:46:44.545
I haven't done nothing wrong.

871
00:46:44.569 --> 00:46:46.147
Well. that's not
what it says here.

872
00:46:46.171 --> 00:46:47.171
What's it say?

873
00:46:49.874 --> 00:46:53.187
It relates to the
successful promotion

874
00:46:53.211 --> 00:46:55.556
of a Detective Sergeant
Larry Peters.

875
00:46:55.580 --> 00:46:56.957
[delightful music playing]

876
00:46:56.981 --> 00:46:59.484
Oh. my God. You had me going.

877
00:47:01.452 --> 00:47:02.520
Congratulations.

878
00:47:06.391 --> 00:47:07.559
Your mum would be proud.

879
00:47:10.328 --> 00:47:11.362
Thank you. Geordie.

880
00:47:12.397 --> 00:47:13.464
Thank you so much.

881
00:47:17.435 --> 00:47:19.604
[man] <i>Bear with me. Mrs Peters.</i>

882
00:47:19.837 --> 00:47:21.172
<i>I have your results.</i>

883
00:47:22.440 --> 00:47:24.051
<i>Ah. it's positive.</i>

884
00:47:24.075 --> 00:47:25.519
<i>Congratulations to you
and your husband.</i>

885
00:47:25.543 --> 00:47:27.478
[all clapping]

886
00:47:31.316 --> 00:47:32.317
[puts down phone]

887
00:47:37.121 --> 00:47:38.957
[faint]
Thank you. Thank you so much.

888
00:47:49.934 --> 00:47:51.169
I didn't catch your name.

889
00:47:52.203 --> 00:47:53.271
No.

890
00:47:54.472 --> 00:47:55.473
You didn't.

891
00:47:59.477 --> 00:48:01.212
[Geordie] I hear you had
quite the journey.

892
00:48:06.217 --> 00:48:07.261
Who were you on the train with?

893
00:48:07.285 --> 00:48:08.485
-Henry Cooper?
-[Alphy sighs]

894
00:48:12.390 --> 00:48:15.159
[sighs] Geordie. I am never
leaving Rochester again.

895
00:48:19.264 --> 00:48:20.331
Come on. then.

896
00:48:32.677 --> 00:48:34.212
You sort things out
with your mum?

897
00:48:36.581 --> 00:48:37.582
She lied to me.

898
00:48:40.251 --> 00:48:41.919
She'd hidden her whole family.

899
00:48:42.487 --> 00:48:43.487
[chuckles softly]

900
00:48:45.423 --> 00:48:46.491
I'm so sorry. Alphy.

901
00:48:48.092 --> 00:48:50.061
I'm obviously not
the son she wanted.

902
00:48:51.462 --> 00:48:52.782
Nor living the life
she hoped for.

903
00:48:55.033 --> 00:48:57.378
It's strange then that
you're so bloody good at it.

904
00:48:57.402 --> 00:49:00.080
Geordie. I couldn't convince
five people on that train

905
00:49:00.104 --> 00:49:01.104
that I was a vicar.

906
00:49:04.375 --> 00:49:05.443
Give over.

907
00:49:06.311 --> 00:49:07.378
Five people.

908
00:49:09.380 --> 00:49:11.015
And the nicest one
was the murderer.

909
00:49:13.051 --> 00:49:14.986
Well. we need to work
on your choice in women.

910
00:49:15.520 --> 00:49:16.521
[chuckles]

911
00:49:18.523 --> 00:49:19.957
Yeah. I need time to think.

912
00:49:21.159 --> 00:49:22.160
And pray.

913
00:49:24.529 --> 00:49:26.006
Okay.

914
00:49:26.030 --> 00:49:27.910
-I'll drop you at the church.
-[engine starts]

915
00:49:28.299 --> 00:49:29.534
Pub first though. right?

916
00:49:30.335 --> 00:49:31.336
Yeah.

917
00:49:39.977 --> 00:49:41.746
[theme music playing]

917
00:49:42.305 --> 00:50:42.746
Do you want subtitles for any video?
